(1. Risk Management Process) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 685.00 Tm
(Risk management is the process of identifying risks, assessing them, and then controlling or) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 671.00 Tm
(reducing them. It is a structured way to protect systems from failure, harm, and loss.) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 655.00 Tm
(Risk identification means finding possible threats such as data leakage, model failure,) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 641.00 Tm
(bias, or security attacks.) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 625.00 Tm
(Risk assessment means estimating how likely a threat is and how serious the impact would be.) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 609.00 Tm
(Risk control or mitigation means taking actions to reduce the probability or impact of those) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 595.00 Tm
(risks.) Tj
ET
BT
0.145 0.388 0.655 rg
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 573.00 Tm
(2. Quantitative Risk Assessment) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 556.00 Tm
(Quantitative risk assessment uses numbers rather than only qualitative judgment.) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 540.00 Tm
(A common framework treats risk as a function of threat probability, success probability of) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 526.00 Tm
(attack, exposure of assets, and asset value.) Tj
ET
BT
0.118 0.125 0.141 rg
/F1 10.5 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 510.00 Tm
(Measurement error is the uncertainty or inaccuracy in estimating these values.) Tj
ET
BT
0.145 0.388 0.655 rg
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 44.00 488.00 Tm
